<section sectnbr = "5B">
<servcat sctnbr = "05" scnbr = "02">
<configtype typenbr = "0">
<servinfotype sitcode = "6">
<servinfo servinfosgmlid = "AENCP70A5206016" svcinfotypenbr = "08" svcinfoqualnbr = "02" page = "2" supplyoff = "1" modify = "1">
<title>
Manual Transaxle Assembly Disassembly and Reassembly
</title>
<servinfosub id = "AENCP70A5206016001">
<title>
Disassembly
</title>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove gear shift &#38; select shaft assembly. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENCP70A5206013"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove input shaft 5th gear and countershaft 5th gear. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENCP70A5206015"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove left case plate bolts (3).
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove left case plate (1) and bearing set shim (2).
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I9P60A521030.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "83.040mm" ver = "01" gw = "160" gh = "219"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove gear shift locating bolts (1) with washers (2), then remove locating spring (3) and steel ball (4).
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove back up light switch (5).
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I9P60A521031.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "80.083mm" ver = "03" gw = "142" gh = "210"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove reverse gear shaft bolt (1) with gasket (2).
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I9P60A521032.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "60.143mm" ver = "01" gw = "131" gh = "154"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove transaxle case bolts (1).
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove transaxle left case (2) from transaxle right case (3) using special tool.
</ptxt>
<servicetool>
<servicetoolitem id = "L5B007">
<s-part>
(A)
</s-part>
<s-number num = "09912-34510">
09912–34510
</s-number>
<ptxt>
</ptxt>
</servicetoolitem>
</servicetool>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I9P60A521033.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "91.810mm" ver = "02" gw = "226" gh = "244"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove reverse gear shift lever bolts (4) and reverse gear shift lever (5).
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Pull out reverse gear shaft (1) with washer (2), then take off reverse idler gear (3).
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Pull out 5th &#38; reverse gear shift guide shaft (6) together with 5th &#38; reverse gear shift shaft (7).
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I4RS0A520033.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "79.279mm" ver = "01" gw = "170" gh = "208"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
By tapping input shaft end with plastic hammer, push it out as assembly from case a little, then remove input shaft assembly (1), countershaft assembly (2), high speed gear shift shaft (3) and low speed gear shift shaft (4) all together.
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I2RH01520035.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "39.994mm" ver = "01" gw = "135" gh = "96"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove countershaft left bearing outer race (1) from transaxle left case (2) using special tool.
</ptxt>
<servicetool>
<servicetoolitem id = "L5B008">
<s-part>
(A)
</s-part>
<s-number num = "09913-84510">
09913–84510
</s-number>
</servicetoolitem>
</servicetool>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I4RS0B521023.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "54.026mm" ver = "01" gw = "124" gh = "137"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove differential gear assembly from transaxle right case.
</ptxt>
</s1>
</servinfosub>
<servinfosub id = "AENCP70A5206016002">
<title>
Reassembly
</title>
<attention2>
<ptxt>
The fastener is pre-coated with friction stabilizer. If the fastener is reused, it may work loose.
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
Replace the fastener pre-coated with friction stabilizer with a new one.
</ptxt>
</attention2>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Install differential assembly into transaxle right case.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Join input shaft assembly (5), countershaft assembly (4), low speed gear shift shaft (2) and high speed gear shift shaft (3) assemblies all together, then install them into transaxle right case (1).
</ptxt>
<attention3>
<ptxt>
Check that countershaft is engaged with final gear.
</ptxt>
</attention3>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I2RH01520080.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "36.522mm" ver = "01" gw = "116" gh = "87"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Install 5th &#38; reverse gear shift shaft (1) with 5th &#38; reverse gear shift guide shaft (2) into transaxle right case (5). Reverse gear shift arm (9) has to be joined with reverse gear shift lever (3) at the same time.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Mate reverse idler gear (6) with reverse gear shift lever (3), insert reverse gear shaft (7) and washer (8) into transaxle right case (5) through idler gear and then align (10) on reverse gear shaft with (11) on transaxle right case.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Tighten new reverse gear shift lever bolts (4) to specified torque.
</ptxt>
<torque>
<torqueitem id = "T5B013">
<t-part>
Reverse gear shift lever bolt
</t-part>
<t-part1>
a
</t-part1>
<t-value1>
23
</t-value1>
<t-value2>
2.3
</t-value2>
<t-value3>
17.0
</t-value3>
</torqueitem>
</torque>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I9P60A521045.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "126.312mm" ver = "01" gw = "169" gh = "342"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Clean mating surfaces of both transaxle right and transaxle left cases, apply sealant to transaxle left case (2) as shown in figure, then mate it with right case (1).
</ptxt>
<materials>
<materialitem name = "SUZUKI Bond No.1217G" id = "M5B007" uid = "-491504098">
<m-part>
“A”
</m-part>
<m-desc>
Sealant
</m-desc>
<m-number>
99000–31260
</m-number>
<m-name>
SUZUKI Bond No.1217G
</m-name>
</materialitem>
</materials>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Tighten transaxle case bolts (3) to specified torque.
</ptxt>
<torque>
<torqueitem id = "T5B014">
<t-part>
Transaxle case bolt
</t-part>
<t-part1>
a
</t-part1>
<t-value1>
23
</t-value1>
<t-value2>
2.3
</t-value2>
<t-value3>
17.0
</t-value3>
</torqueitem>
</torque>
<figure page = "2">
<graphic graphicname = "I9P60A521034.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "161.665mm" ver = "01" gw = "204" gh = "442"/>
<callout>
<table frame = "all" colsep = "1" rowsep = "1">
<tgroup cols = "2" colsep = "1" rowsep = "1">
