</tbody>
</tgroup>
</table>
</callout>
</figure>
</s2>
<s2>
<ptxt>
Remove left case plate.
</ptxt>
</s2>
<s2>
<ptxt>
Place straightedge (1) over shim (3) and compress it by hand through straightedge, and measure “a” using feeler gauge (2).
</ptxt>
<spec>
<title>
Clearance between case surface and straightedge
</title>
<ptxt>
“a”: 0.18 – 0.22 mm (0.0071 – 0.0087 in.)
</ptxt>
</spec>
</s2>
<s2>
<ptxt>
If clearance “a” is out of specification, select suitable shim which adjusts clearance “a” to specification and put it on bearing outer race.
</ptxt>
</s2>
<attention3>
<ptxt>
